## ‚úÖ DO (Recommended Practices)

### 1. Semantic HTML

- ‚úÖ **Use semantic elements**: Prefer semantic HTML5 elements over generic divs
- ‚úÖ **Meaningful structure**: Structure content with appropriate semantic tags
- ‚úÖ **Clear hierarchy**: Maintain logical heading hierarchy (h1 ‚Üí h2 ‚Üí h3)

**Example:**
```html
<!-- ‚úÖ Correct: Semantic structure -->
<article>
  <header>
    <h1>Article Title</h1>
    <p class="meta">Published on <time datetime="2024-01-15">January 15, 2024</time></p>
  </header>
  <section>
    <h2>Introduction</h2>
    <p>Content here...</p>
  </section>
  <footer>
    <p>Author: John Doe</p>
  </footer>
</article>
```

### 2. Accessibility (a11y)

- ‚úÖ **Alt text for images**: Always provide descriptive alt text
- ‚úÖ **ARIA attributes**: Use ARIA when semantic HTML is insufficient
- ‚úÖ **Keyboard navigation**: Ensure all interactive elements are keyboard accessible
- ‚úÖ **Form labels**: Always associate labels with form inputs
- ‚úÖ **Landmarks**: Use semantic landmarks (header, nav, main, footer, aside)
- ‚úÖ **Skip links**: Provide skip links for keyboard navigation
- ‚úÖ **Focus management**: Ensure visible focus indicators
- ‚úÖ **Form validation**: Use HTML5 validation attributes (required, pattern, min, max)
- ‚úÖ **Empty alt for decorative images**: Use alt="" for purely decorative images

**Example:**
```html
<!-- ‚úÖ Correct: Skip link -->
<a href="#main-content" class="skip-link">Skip to main content</a>

<!-- ‚úÖ Correct: Accessible form with validation -->
<form>
  <label for="email">Email Address</label>
  <input 
    type="email" 
    id="email" 
    name="email" 
    required 
    aria-describedby="email-help email-error"
    aria-invalid="false"
    pattern="[a-z0-9._%+-]+@[a-z0-9.-]+\.[a-z]{2,}$"
  >
  <small id="email-help">We'll never share your email.</small>
  <span id="email-error" role="alert" aria-live="polite"></span>
  
  <label for="age">Age</label>
  <input 
    type="number" 
    id="age" 
    name="age" 
    min="18" 
    max="120" 
    required
    aria-describedby="age-help"
  >
  <small id="age-help">Must be between 18 and 120</small>
  
  <button type="submit">Submit</button>
</form>

<!-- ‚úÖ Correct: Accessible image -->
<img 
  src="chart.png" 
  alt="Sales chart showing 25% increase in Q4 2024"
  loading="lazy"
  width="800"
  height="600"
>

<!-- ‚úÖ Correct: Decorative image -->
<img 
  src="decoration.png" 
  alt=""
  role="presentation"
>
```

### 3. Modern HTML5 Features

- ‚úÖ **Use HTML5 elements**: article, section, nav, header, footer, aside, main
- ‚úÖ **Input types**: Use appropriate input types (email, tel, url, date, etc.)
- ‚úÖ **Data attributes**: Use data-* attributes for custom data
- ‚úÖ **Essential meta tags**: Include charset, viewport, and title

**Example:**
```html
