```

### 4. Basic Performance

- ‚úÖ **Lazy loading**: Use loading="lazy" for images below the fold
- ‚úÖ **Defer scripts**: Use defer or async for non-critical scripts
- ‚úÖ **Minimize inline styles**: Prefer external stylesheets
- ‚úÖ **Valid HTML**: Ensure HTML validates against W3C standards
- ‚úÖ **Image dimensions**: Always specify width and height for images

**Example:**
```html
<!-- ‚úÖ Correct: Optimized image loading -->
<img 
  src="hero.jpg" 
  alt="Hero image"
  loading="eager"
  width="1200"
  height="600"
>

<img 
  src="thumbnail.jpg" 
  alt="Thumbnail"
  loading="lazy"
  width="200"
  height="200"
>

<!-- ‚úÖ Correct: Script loading -->
<script src="critical.js" defer></script>
<script src="analytics.js" async></script>
```

## ‚ùå DON'T (Forbidden Practices)

### 1. Avoid Non-Semantic HTML

- ‚ùå **Don't use divs for everything**: Avoid div soup
- ‚ùå **Don't skip semantic elements**: Don't use generic containers when semantic elements exist
- ‚ùå **Don't break heading hierarchy**: Don't skip heading levels (h1 ‚Üí h3)
- ‚ùå **Don't nest main incorrectly**: Don't nest `<main>` inside `<article>` or `<section>` - `<main>` should be direct child of `<body>`

**Example:**
```html
<!-- ‚ùå Incorrect: Div soup -->
<div>
  <div>
    <div>Title</div>
    <div>Content</div>
  </div>
</div>

<!-- ‚ùå Incorrect: Main nested incorrectly -->
<article>
  <main>
    <p>Content</p>
  </main>
</article>

<!-- ‚úÖ Correct: Semantic structure -->
<body>
  <article>
    <header>
      <h1>Title</h1>
    </header>
    <section>
      <p>Content</p>
    </section>
  </article>
  <main>
    <p>Main content</p>
  </main>
</body>
```

### 2. Accessibility Anti-patterns

- ‚ùå **Don't skip alt text**: Never omit alt attribute on images (use alt="" for decorative images)
- ‚ùå **Don't use divs for buttons**: Use button or anchor elements
- ‚ùå **Don't create inaccessible forms**: Always associate labels with inputs
- ‚ùå **Don't rely on color alone**: Don't convey information only through color
- ‚ùå **Don't use inline event handlers**: Avoid onclick, onsubmit, etc. - use event listeners
- ‚ùå **Don't skip form validation**: Use HTML5 validation attributes

**Example:**
```html
<!-- ‚ùå Incorrect: Missing accessibility -->
<img src="chart.png">
<div onclick="submit()">Submit</div>
<input type="text" name="email">

<!-- ‚ùå Incorrect: Inline event handler -->
<button onclick="handleClick()">Click me</button>

<!-- ‚úÖ Correct: Accessible -->
<img src="chart.png" alt="Sales data visualization" width="800" height="600">
<button type="submit" id="submit-btn">Submit</button>
<script>
  document.getElementById('submit-btn').addEventListener('click', submit);
</script>
<label for="email">Email</label>
<input type="email" id="email" name="email" required>
```

### 3. Outdated Practices

- ‚ùå **Don't use deprecated tags**: Avoid center, font, marquee, etc.
- ‚ùå **Don't use inline styles excessively**: Minimize inline CSS
- ‚ùå **Don't use table layouts**: Don't use tables for page layout
- ‚ùå **Don't skip DOCTYPE**: Always include proper DOCTYPE
- ‚ùå **Don't skip viewport meta**: Always include viewport meta tag

**Example:**
