## üìù Key Points

### Must Have
- ‚úÖ **Semantic HTML**: Always use semantic HTML5 elements
- ‚úÖ **Accessibility**: Ensure WCAG 2.1 AA compliance minimum
- ‚úÖ **Valid HTML**: HTML must validate against W3C standards
- ‚úÖ **Proper DOCTYPE**: Always include `<!DOCTYPE html>`
- ‚úÖ **Language attribute**: Always specify `lang` attribute on html element
- ‚úÖ **Viewport meta**: Always include viewport meta tag for responsive design
- ‚úÖ **Charset meta**: Always include charset meta tag (UTF-8)
- ‚úÖ **Title tag**: Always include descriptive title tag

### Do
- ‚úÖ Use semantic elements (article, section, nav, header, footer, main, aside)
- ‚úÖ Provide alt text for all images (empty alt="" for decorative images)
- ‚úÖ Associate labels with all form inputs
- ‚úÖ Use appropriate ARIA attributes when needed
- ‚úÖ Validate HTML syntax
- ‚úÖ Use modern HTML5 input types
- ‚úÖ Implement lazy loading for images
- ‚úÖ Ensure keyboard navigation works
- ‚úÖ Include viewport meta tag
- ‚úÖ Add skip links for keyboard navigation
- ‚úÖ Use HTML5 form validation attributes
- ‚úÖ Always specify image dimensions (width/height)

### Don't
- ‚ùå Don't create div soup - use semantic elements
- ‚ùå Don't skip heading hierarchy
- ‚ùå Don't omit alt text on images (use alt="" for decorative images)
- ‚ùå Don't use divs for interactive elements (use button, a, etc.)
- ‚ùå Don't create forms without labels
- ‚ùå Don't rely on color alone for information
- ‚ùå Don't use deprecated HTML tags
- ‚ùå Don't use tables for layout
- ‚ùå Don't skip DOCTYPE declaration
- ‚ùå Don't skip viewport meta tag
- ‚ùå Don't nest main element inside article or section
- ‚ùå Don't use inline event handlers (onclick, onsubmit, etc.)
- ‚ùå Don't forget to specify image dimensions (width/height)

